No fewer than 18 stranded Nigerians in some European countries will arrive on Friday, The Nation has learnt. According to the Nigerian Diaspora Commission (NIDCOM) the chartered flight is at the expense of Total oil. The flight departed Paris at about 8am on Friday morning
.
The tweet from NIDCOM reads: “About 18 Stranded Nigerians in some European Countries just departed citizenM Paris Charles de Gaulle Airport in Paris, 8 a.m to Murtala Muhammed Int’l Airport Lagos in a repatriation exercise coordinated by the Nigerian Mission in France monitored by NiDCOM.”